  <brief_title>Vasoactive Hormones and Oxygen Saturation During Apneic Events in Patients With Obstructive Sleep Apnea</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Regional Hospital Holstebro</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Regional Hospital Holstebro</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The mechanisms involved in development and maintenance of hypertension in obstructive sleep
      apnea are not clarified.

      We hypothesize that patients with obstructive sleep apnea have an abnormal level of some
      vasoactive hormones during apneic events during sleep.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
